1. What is Amazon EKS?

Amazon EKS (Elastic Kubernetes Service) is a managed Kubernetes service provided by AWS.

With EKS:

AWS manages the Kubernetes control plane.
You manage worker nodes or use serverless nodes with Fargate.
Highly available and scalable.
Integrated with IAM, VPC, CloudWatch, and ELB.

Benefits of EKS
No need to manage Kubernetes master nodes.
Automatic patching and upgrades.
Secure integration with AWS services.
Production-ready.


